    .b-usage.b-content
        .section
            h2.form-item Basic usage

            .b-usage__text At first, add <span class="textBlue">jquery.phone-highlight.js</span> into your <span class="textPurple">&lt;head></span>.
                br
                br
                | Then, put following into in you <span class="textBlue">main.js</span>:

            .form-item
                pre.
                    <code class="javascript">$('p.containing-phones').phoneHighlight();</code>

            .b-usage__text Or with <span class="textBlue">mobile-detect.js</span>

            .form-item
                pre.
                    <code class="javascript">var md = new MobileDetect(window.navigator.userAgent);
                    if (md.mobile()) {
                        $('.phones').phoneHighlight();
                    }</code>

            .b-usage__text Plugin will replace text phones with <span class="textPurple">&lt;a></span> tag.

            .form-item
                pre.
                    <code class="html">Lorem ipsum dolor &lt;a href="tel:+73812786644" class="phone">+7 (3812) 78-66-44&lt;/a></code>

            .b-usage__text NOTE! Do not execute plugin on whole body or other huge/interactive parts of the page! It may break other scripts or cause perfomance issues.

    .b-demo.b-content
        .section
            h2 Configuring

            p.textLg Plugin have 3 options which can be passed into its call:
            
            .form-item
                pre.
                    <code class="javascript">$('.phone').phoneHighlight({
                        countrycode: '+7',
                        citycode: '3812',
                        minLenWithoutCodes: 7
                    });</code>
            br
            h2 How it works

            .textLg
                | It tooks text content of marked nodes and removes all symbols excepting digits and leading plus sign.
                br
                br
                | Then plugin checks format of obtained result. There are 2 possible cases:

                ol
                    li Current result already starts with plus sign or its length is greater than <span class="textPurple">minLenWithoutCodes</span> option value. In this case <span class="textPurple">countrycode</span> and <span class="textPurple">citycode</span> won't be added to phone.
                    li Otherwise phone will be concatinated with <span class="textPurple">countrycode</span> and <span class="textPurple">citycode</span> Note, that default values of <span class="textPurple">countrycode</span> and <span class="textPurple">citycode</span> options is empty strings.

                | You can also override global code options by setting appropriate <span class="textPurple">data</span> attributes:

            .form-item
                pre.
                    <code class="html">&lt;span class="phone" data-countrycode="+1" data-citycode="123">999-44-22&lt;/span></code>
            br
            h2 Running tests
            p.textLg At firts, you have to install dependencies by running <span class="textGreen">npm install</span> and <span class="textGreen">bower install</span>. Now execute <span class="textGreen">npm run test</span> command.

